comment.narrative:
1. ZEC Strategic Plan was developed and is being implemented with the first major step being development of a new VR system, undertaking extensive stakeholder consultations and creative voter education campaign;
2. Capacity and training needs assessment was completed and its recommendations are being implemented.
3. Four Options for voter registration systems were developed resulting in the selection of the BVR option by ZEC after consultation with election stakeholders. Specifications for BVR kits were developed on the basis of which procurement of the 3,000 kits was undertaken. With technical support of UNDP ZEC trained 8,500 BVR kit operators and started a country wide roll out of the BVR resulting in 3 500 000 voters registered over the past three months under the new system against a target of 7 000 000 voters. This is highly significant progress for the Project.
4. With UNDP technical support ZEC together with Civil Society Organizations developed and undertook a BVR Voter Education campaign. This included design and printing of materials (600,000 posters, 1,400,000 leaflets, 157,500 stickers, 1,000 newsletters), use of electronic media, road shows, establishment of a call centre and use of an SMS platform. The campaign is being monitored to ensure its effectiveness and getting feedback for making improvements. The BVR Voter education has reached millions of citizens as follows:
a)	SMS approximately 5 million people;
b)	Printed Materials approximately 2 million people;
c)	Radio approximately 7 million people;
d)	Road Shows approximately 160,000 people (80 road shows x 2,000 people per road show);

5. Stakeholder engagement between the Zimbabwe Electoral Commission and political parties, CSOs, FBOs and Media were established and they have been meeting regularly and UNDP through creating this platform facilitated engagement among key stakeholders for the first time in an electoral cycle in Zimbabwe. This opportunity and platform has enable amicable and cordial

1.a. The platform convenes at least one policy dialogue on issues of peace and social cohesion (including on the NPRC Bill, SDG 16); 
1.b. A draft coordination framework is developed and adopted; At least 2 coordination events convened;
2.a	NPRC Commissioners equipped with strategic competencies and skills. Awareness raising on the NPRC mandate and functions;
2.b  A tailored NPRC Capacity Development Plan is designed and implementation ; Strategic plan to guide the work of the NPRC is designed;
2.c  At least 4 draft internal organizational tools are developed (including a Gender and Diversity Management Policy);
2.d A working group is established to design the CEWER mechanism; 
3.a.	A draft framework for consensus building on shared values is designed; At least 4 high level consensus building sessions held through dialogue platforms
 4.a  At least 75 LPCs (cumulative); 75 PM (cumulative); 30 Peace Dividend Programmes
4.b  A dispute management system is piloted to document at least 20 cases;

